  "datePublished": "2025-12-26",
  "description": "A presheaf on a category C is a contravariant [functor](../../../objects/categories/ordinary-categories/terms/functor.md) F: C^op → Set. It assigns a set F(U) of \"sections\" to each object U and a [restriction](./restriction.md) map F(U) → F(V) to each [morphism](../../../objects/categories/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism.md) V → U, preserving composition and identity.",
